{"type":"message","id":"b28c4716","parentId":"c967ff99","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:20:24.240Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_19motwsfbbar_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 2274\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=777\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 082009 - The TIC Experiment is the next critical action to advance Phase 1. I need to examine the existing pulse logs to understand their format before implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\n\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"delta-atlas","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 2274\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=777\n[mutation proposed] research/TIC-EXPERIMENT.md\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 082009 - The TIC Experiment is the next critical action to advance Phase 1. I need to examine the existing pulse logs to understand their format before implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354824239}}
{"type":"message","id":"54730db4","parentId":"b28c4716","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:20:24.248Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_19motwsfbbar_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 081716\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- There's a new insight about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- Next action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n\r\nThe pending action is:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to implement the TIC classifier. This is a file edit - I should create a script or update a file that implements this.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist. The recent pulse log is `pulse_2026-03-24 081616.md` in the logs directory.\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I should:\r\n1. Create a script that reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content across pulses\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nThe most concrete action would be to create a Python script or PowerShell script that implements the TIC classifier. Given the context (PowerShell wrapper, .ps1 files), I should probably create a PowerShell script for the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the architecture, the LLM is being called via pulse.ps1. For the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Create a TIC implementation\r\n2. Run it on existing pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step: Create a TIC classifier script. I'll make it a PowerShell script that reads pulse logs and identifies invariants vs variants.\r\n\r\nLet me create a script `tic_classifier.ps1` that:\r\n- Reads pulse logs from `logs/` directory\r\n- Extracts content patterns\r\n\r\n\r\n- Classifies as invariant (stable across pulses) or variant (changes between pulses)\r\n- Attempts prediction\r\n\r\nI'll focus on creating a structured approach to identify and classify pulse content systematically.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the immediate next step to validate the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. I need to implement a classifier that identifies invariants across pulse logs and tests if these invariants can predict subsequent pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.ps1` - the core TIC implementation that reads pulse logs, extracts content patterns, classifies invariant vs variant elements, and measures prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC - Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\n# Tests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$MinPulseCount = 5,\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$script:InvariantCount = 0\r\n$script:VariantCount = 0\r\n$script:CorrectPredictions = 0\r\n$script:TotalPredictions = 0\r\n\r\nfunction Extract-ContentTokens {\r\n    param([string]$Content)\r\n    # Extract meaningful tokens: headings, key phrases, file references\r\n    $tokens = @()\r\n    \r\n    # Headings\r\n    $headings = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?m)^##?\\s+(.+)$') | ForEach-Object { $_.Groups[1].Value }\r\n    $tokens += $headings\r\n    \r\n    # File references\r\n    $files = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?:\\.md|\\.ps1|\\.json|\\.yaml)(?:\\s|$|[^a-z])') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $tokens += $files\r\n    \r\n    # Goal/phase keywords\r\n    $keywords = [regex]::Matches($Content, '(?i)(phase|goal|complete|pending|task|insight|hypothesis)') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value.ToLower() }\r\n    $tokens += $keywords\r\n    \r\n    return $tokens | Sort-Object -Unique\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Compare-Pulses {\r\n    param([array]$Tokens1, [array]$Tokens2)\r\n    \r\n    $common = @($Tokens1 | Where-Object { $Tokens2 -contains $_ })\r\n    $only1 = @($Tokens1 | Where-Object { $Tokens2 -notcontains $_ })\r\n    \r\n    return @{\r\n        Invariant = $common\r\n        Variant = $only1\r\n        Similarity = if ($Tokens1.Count -gt 0) { $common.Count / $Tokens1.Count } else { 0 }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Classify-Token {\r\n    param([string]$Token, [hashtable]$History)\r\n    \r\n    # Count occurrences across history\r\n    $count = 0\r\n    foreach ($snapshot in $History.Values) {\r\n        if ($snapshot -contains $Token) { $count++ }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $stability = $count / $History.Count\r\n    return @{\r\n        Token = $Token\r\n        Stability = $stability\r\n        Classification = if ($stability -ge 0.7) { \"INVARIANT\" } else { \"VARIANT\" }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction Predict-NextPulse {\r\n    param([array]$Invariants, [string]$NextContent)\r\n    \r\n    $nextTokens = Extract-ContentTokens -Content $NextContent\r\n    $predictedTokens = $Invariants | Where-Object { $_ -ne \"\" }\r\n    \r\n    $hits = @($nextTokens | Where-Object { $predictedTokens -contains $_ })\r\n    $accuracy = if ($nextTokens.Count -gt 0) { $hits.Count / $nextTokens.Count } else { \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 08:17:47\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354824245}}
