{"type":"message","id":"b3efe3df","parentId":"6220711e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:05.990Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting - there's already a TIC-EXPERIMENT.md and TIC_RESULTS.md. Let me read those to understand what's already been done. Let me also check the ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md and COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md to understand the big picture.","thinkingSignature":"5ac34a228a90bfdbffe26994729cde727f73e5adefdb98ce6c653c40472411d9"},{"type":"text","text":"There's already TIC work done. Let me check what's there:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8hz05qoema5a_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC_RESULTS.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8hz05qoema5a_2","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\research\\TIC-EXPERIMENT.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":4602,"output":153,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16892,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774354861888}}
{"type":"message","id":"e21ecde8","parentId":"b3efe3df","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:06.005Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8hz05qoema5a_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TIC Experiment Results — 2026-03-23 10:05\n\n## Setup\n- Pulse logs analyzed: 25\n- Time range: 03/22/2026 01:28:32 → 03/23/2026 07:04:18\n- Invariant threshold: streak >= 3 consecutive pulses\n- Variant threshold: streak <= 1\n\n## Invariant Classification\n- Invariant elements (streak >= 3): 8\n- Variant elements (streak <= 1): 0\n- Key invariants: pulse, Phase 1, Sandbox, Breakaway, Phase 0, GAP, llm, TemporalAttention\n\n## Prediction Test\n- Pairs evaluated: 21\n- Mean Precision: 90%\n- Mean Recall: 88.5%\n- Random baseline: ~5%\n- Result: BETTER THAN RANDOM\n\n## Gap Sensitivity\n- Small gaps (<30 min) Jaccard: 0.704\n- Medium gaps (30-120m) Jaccard: 1\n- Large gaps (>120 min) Jaccard: 0.834\n- Hypothesis (shorter gap → more overlap): REJECTED\n\n## Phase Persistence\n  Phase 0 COMPLETE: streak=17   Phase 1 COMPLETE: streak=17\n\n## TIC Score: 2/3\n## VERDICT: SUPPORTED\n\n## Implications\n- If SUPPORTED: compression=causal hypothesis is empirically grounded for Breakaway pulses\n- Invariant elements = causal anchors (Phase status, research topic persistence)\n- Gap size can be used to weight reconstruction confidence\n- Next: Use invariants as fixed points in compression, treat variants as contingent details\n\n## Next Experiment\n- Train actual embedding-based compressor on Paperspace GPU\n- Measure: does cosine similarity between pulse embeddings correlate with Jaccard?\n- Success criteria: >60% next-pulse prediction using only embedding dot products\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774354866002}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b8ddaca","parentId":"e21ecde8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T12:21:06.009Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8hz05qoema5a_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n**Created:** 2026-03-23\r\n**Status:** READY TO RUN\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCausal structure = invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\r\n\r\n## Method\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Collect Pulse Logs\r\n```powershell\r\nGet-ChildItem logs/*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 20\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Extract Content Features\r\nFor each pulse, extract:\r\n- Topic keywords (nouns/verbs)\r\n- File references\r\n- Question marks (open problems)\r\n- Action items (verbs in imperative)\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compute Invariants\r\nFind features that persist across multiple pulses (invariant = appears in Ã¢â€°Â¥3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 4: Compute Variants\r\nFind features unique to single pulses or clusters (variant = appears in <3 pulses).\r\n\r\n### Step 5: Predict Next Pulse\r\nUsing invariant/variant classification, predict which features appear in pulse N+1.\r\n\r\n## Success Criteria\r\n- **Classification:** >70% invariant/variant accuracy\r\n- **Prediction:** >60% next-pulse feature recall\r\n\r\n## Log Inventory\r\n| Pulse | Date | Key Content |\r\n|-------|------|-------------|\r\n| (to be populated) | | |\r\n\r\n## Results (TBD)\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure â€” compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Implementation\n\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/Variant classification accuracy: >70%\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\n\n## Data\n- Source: `logs/pulse_*.md` (20+ pulse logs)\n- Target: Last pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 145438.md`\n```\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Objective\nTest if >70% of pulse content can be classified as invariant/variant, and if invariants can predict next-pulse content with >60% accuracy.\n\n## Method\n1. Tokenize pulse logs into content blocks\n2. Classify each block as INVARIANT (appears in multiple pulses) or VARIANT (unique)\n3. Build invariant graph showing which blocks co-occur\n4. Predict next pulse from invariant sequence\n5. Validate against ground truth\n\n## Status\n- [x] Script created: `src/tic_classifier.py`\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulse logs\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n## Phase 1 Advancement: Compression-Causal Duality Validation\n\n**Hypothesis:** Causal structure IS invariant structure â€” compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n**Success Criteria:**\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\n\n## Experiment Design\n\n### Step 1: Extract Pulse Features\nFrom each `logs/pulse_*.md`:\n- Goals mentioned (persistent vs new)\n- File references (repeated vs unique)\n- Action patterns (routine vs novel)\n- Insight keywords (reinforced vs first-occurrence)\n\n### Step 2: Classify Invariants\n- **INVARIANT:** Pattern appears in â‰¥3 consecutive pulses\n- **VARIANT:** Pattern appears in <3 pulses or changes form\n\n### Step 3: Predict Next Pulse\nFrom invariants in pulse N, predict:\n- Which goals will persist\n- Which files will be referenced\n- Which actions will repeat\n\n### Step 4: Validate\nCompare predictions against actual pulse N+1 content.\n\n## Implementation Status\n- [ ] Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\n- [ ] Compute invariant/variant classifications\n- [ ] Generate next-pulse predictions\n- [ ] Measure accuracy vs success criteria\n- [ ] Document results in `research/TIC-RESULTS.md`\n\n## Pulse Log Analysis (Last 20)\n```\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n# Phase: Phase 1 Advancement - COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\n# Created: 2026-03-24\n# Goal: Validate that causal structure = invariant structure\n\n## Hypothesis\nAn LLM that can identify temporal invariants across pulse logs has discovered causal relationships.\nCompression that preserves invariants IS causal discovery.\n\n## Method\n1. Extract features from last 20 pulse logs\n2. Classify each feature as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) or VARIANT (changing)\n3. Use invariants to predict next pulse content\n4. Measure accuracy against success criteria\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n## Implementation\n# See: experiments/tic_classifier.py\n\n## Pulse Log Files (n=20)\n- logs/pulse_2026-03-*.md\n\n## Results (to be filled)\n- classification_accuracy: pending\n- prediction_accuracy: pending\n- invariants_found: []\n- variants_found: []\n\n## Next Steps\n1. Run TIC classifier on pulse logs\n2. Validate against success criteria\n3. If pass: Phase 1 and Phase 2 collapse into unified TIC problem\n4. If fail: Refine Î» parameter and retry\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n## Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\n\n## Experiment Design\n- **Goal**: Test if invariant/variant classification >70% and next-pulse prediction >60%\n- **Method**: Analyze pulse logs for recurring patterns vs unique content\n\n## Classification Criteria\n\n### Invariants (persistent across pulses)\n- File paths and directory structures\n- Core architecture decisions\n- Active/completed phases\n- Pending action items (stable across sessions)\n\n### Variants (session-specific)\n- Timestamps and dates\n- Specific numbers (counts, ratios)\n- Observations about current state\n- Newly added items\n\n## Log Analysis\n\n### Pulse log structure to extract:\n- Goals section (stable → invariant)\n- Pending actions (relatively stable → invariant)\n- Recent history (variant → session-specific)\n- Notes (mixed → need classification)\n\n## Success Metrics\n- [ ] >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- [ ] >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\n\n## Implementation Plan\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\n2. Extract goal/pending content\n3. Classify each line as invariant or variant\n4. Measure classification accuracy (manual validation sample)\n5. Predict next pulse goals from invariants\n6. Compare prediction to actual next pulse\n\n---\n*Created: 2026-03-24*\n*Status: IN PROGRESS*\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n\nAnalyzes pulse logs to classify content as INVARIANT (stable across sessions) vs VARIANT (changes between sessions).\n\n## Hypothesis\n- Invariant content = causal structure (persists, enables prediction)\n- Variant content = noise/accident (ephemeral details)\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction from invariants\n\n## Approach\n1. Parse pulse logs for content tokens\n2. Compare adjacent pulse logs for changes\n3. Classify tokens: INVARIANT if appears in N≥3 consecutive sessions\n4. Validate by predicting next pulse content from learned invariants\n\n## TODO\n- [ ] Implement log parser\n- [ ] Build token frequency table across sessions\n- [ ] Classify invariant/variant tokens (threshold: N≥3)\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\n- [ ] Test next-pulse prediction from invariants\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria\n\n---\n*Created: 2026-03-24 for Phase 1 TIC Experiment*\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n**Created:** 2026-03-24  \n**Status:** RUNNING\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure = invariant structure. Compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Method\n1. Collect last N pulse logs (N=20)\n2. Extract token-level features across all logs\n3. Classify each token/phrase as **invariant** (stable across sessions) or **variant** (session-specific)\n4. Use invariant structure to predict next pulse content\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/variant classification: >70% accuracy\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60% accuracy\n\n## Implementation\nSee `src/tic-classifier.ps1`\n\n## Results\n| Metric | Target | Actual | Status |\n|--------|--------|--------|--------|\n| Invariant classification | >70% | TBD | ⏳ |\n| Variant classification | >70% | TBD | ⏳ |\n| Next-pulse prediction | >60% | TBD | ⏳ |\n\n## Next Steps\n- [ ] Run classifier on logs/pulse_*.md\n- [ ] Validate predictions against actual next pulse\n- [ ] Tune λ based on results\n- [ ] Document findings in COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n\n## Overview\nTest hypothesis: **Causal structure IS invariant structure** - compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Methodology\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs from `logs/pulse_*.md`\n2. Extract feature vectors from each pulse (file modifications, goal references, concepts)\n3. Classify each feature as **invariant** (stable across pulses) or **variant** (changing)\n4. Use invariant set to predict next pulse content\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\n\n## Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\n\n## Implementation Plan\n- [ ] Parse pulse logs and extract feature corpus\n- [ ] Implement invariant/variant classifier\n- [ ] Build next-pulse predictor from invariants\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulses\n- [ ] Validate against criteria\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway's stateless nature means each pulse is independent\n- Invariants = persistent structure across discontinuity\n- Variants = pulse-specific content\n\"\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC: Temporal Invariance Compression Experiment\n\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure. A compressor that discovers invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Method\n1. **Tokenize** each pulse into conceptual units (sentences, code blocks, key-value pairs)\n2. **Compare** token sets across consecutive pulses\n3. **Classify** tokens as:\n   - **INVARIANT**: Present in multiple pulses (stable state)\n   - **VARIANT**: Unique to single pulse (novel content)\n4. **Predict** next pulse: reconstruct from accumulated invariants\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/variant classification accuracy: >70%\n- Next-pulse prediction accuracy: >60%\n\n## Implementation Approach\n\n\n## Data Sources\n- Pulse logs: `logs/pulse_*.md`\n- Reference: `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`\n\n## Status\n- [ ] Implement tokenizer\n- [ ] Build invariant detection\n- [ ] Run on last 20 pulse logs\n- [ ] Measure classification accuracy\n- [ ] Measure prediction accuracy\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria\n\n## Expected Outcome\nIf >70% of pulse content is correctly classified as invariant/variant AND >60% of next pulse content is correctly predicted from invariants, the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis is validated.\n```\r\n\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\n## Hypothesis\nCausal structure IS invariant structure — compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n## Methodology\n1. Parse last 20 pulse logs\n2. Extract content tokens (goals, actions, insights, file references)\n3. Classify each token as INVARIANT (recurs across sessions) or VARIANT (session-specific)\n4. Predict next pulse content from invariant set\n5. Measure accuracy against success criteria\n\n## Success Criteria\n- Invariant/variant classification: >70% accuracy\n- Next-pulse prediction: >60% accuracy\n\n## Log Analysis\n\n### Pulse Log Format\nEach pulse log contains:\n- Observation (1-2 sentences)\n- Action (file 